# WorthIT – Data Flow & Listing Model

## 🎯 Overview

This document defines the core data model and system flow for the WorthIT project.

The goal is to create a system that:

* Collects second-hand listings
* Normalizes them into a unified structure
* Analyzes them based on market data
* Returns a deal evaluation (score + verdict)

---

## 🔄 System Flow

1. User inputs search query
   Example:
   "iPhone 13 יד שנייה"

2. System retrieves listings (future: Playwright scraping)

3. Listings are normalized into a unified structure (`Listing`)

4. Listings are analyzed:

   * Market comparison
   * Statistical calculations
   * Score generation

5. System returns analyzed listings to the extension/UI client

---

## 📦 Core Data Model – Listing

This is the main object used across the entire system.

```ts
type Listing = {
  id: string;

  title: string;
  price: number;
  currency: "ILS" | "USD";

  source: "facebook" | "yad2";

  url?: string;
  image?: string;

  location?: string;
  condition?: "new" | "used";

  extractedAt: Date;
};
```

---

## 🧠 Notes on Fields

### id

* Unique identifier for the listing
* Used for React keys and database storage

---

### title

* Raw title from the listing
* Used for:

  * Display
  * Product extraction
  * Condition detection

---

### price

* Must be normalized to number
* Remove currency symbols before parsing

---

### source

Defines origin platform:

* "facebook"
* "yad2"

---

### url

* Link to the original listing
* Used for user navigation

---

### image

* Main product image
* Improves UI significantly

---

### condition (Derived Field)

Condition is NOT directly provided by most sources.

It must be extracted from text.

Example logic:

```ts
function extractCondition(title: string): "new" | "used" | undefined {
  const lower = title.toLowerCase();

  if (lower.includes("חדש") || lower.includes("new")) return "new";

  if (lower.includes("יד 2") || lower.includes("יד שניה") || lower.includes("used")) return "used";

  return undefined;
}
```

---

### extractedAt

* Timestamp of when the data was collected
* Useful for caching and freshness

---

## 📊 Analyzed Listing Model

After processing, listings are enriched:

```ts
type AnalyzedListing = Listing & {
  marketMedian: number;
  score: number;
  verdict: "Good" | "Fair" | "Bad";
};
```

---

## ⚙️ Analysis Flow

Function to implement:

```ts
analyzeListings(listings: Listing[]): AnalyzedListing[]
```

Steps:

1. Extract prices
2. Remove outliers
3. Calculate:

   * median
   * average
4. Compare each listing to market median
5. Generate:

   * score
   * verdict

---

## 🚫 Important Constraints

* Do NOT implement scraping yet
* Do NOT depend on Facebook Marketplace or Yad2 APIs
* Use static or controlled data during development

---

## 🕷️ Future: Playwright Integration

Later, listings will be fetched using:

* Playwright (browser automation)

Targets:

* Facebook Marketplace
* Yad2

Important:

* Scraping layer must ONLY return `Listing[]`
* No analysis logic inside scraping

